{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","title":"fill(count:cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fill","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"count"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize","text":"gssize"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"gssize","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:3GIO27BufferedInputStreamProtocolPAAE4fill5count11cancellableS2i_AA14CancellableRefVSgtKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO19BufferedInputStreamC","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStream\/fill(count:cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fill","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize","text":"gssize","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gssize","preciseIdentifier":"c:glibconfig.h@T@gssize"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" is zero, returns zero and does nothing. A value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"larger than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MAXSSIZE"},{"text":" will cause a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[error"},{"code":"Gio.IOErrorEnum.INVALID_ARGUMENT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On success, the number of bytes read into the buffer is returned."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file. Zero is returned on end of file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(or if "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is zero),  but never otherwise."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" is -1 then the attempted read size is equal to the number of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"bytes that are required to fill the buffer."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"was cancelled, the error [error","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.IOErrorEnum.CANCELLED"},{"type":"text","text":"] will be returned."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If an operation was partially finished when the operation was cancelled the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"partial result will be returned, without an error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On error ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-1"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is set accordingly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the asynchronous, non-blocking, version of this function, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.BufferedInputStream.fill_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStream","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStream\/BufferedInputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tries to read "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes from the stream into the buffer."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Will block during this read.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/bufferedinputstream\/fill(count:cancellable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/BufferedInputStream/fill(count:cancellable:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/BufferedInputStream\/fill(count:cancellable:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Tries to read ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" bytes from the stream into the buffer.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Will block during this read.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fill"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalPa